-1 0 DEATH CORPSE MORGUE~
When your character dies, your spirit is reincarnated back to the
altar of the temple in your hometown. Your {&corpse{x is left behind
in the room that you were killed in, along with all of your things.
{x
After you die, you become a '{#ghost{x' for the next few game hours,
during which time nothing will attack you.  This allows you to
retrieve your equipment when you are killed by an aggressive mobile.
If you do not retrieve your corpse in time, it will decay and all
of your belongings will show up in the {&donation pit{x. ({!15{x minutes is
about how long it takes for your corpse to decay.)
{x 
Death does not affect groups or those following you.
{x
You lose roughly 2/3's of the experience you had earned towards your
next level, and every third death you lose one point of constitution.
Constitution lost due to dying is retrainable.

Heroes may buy constitution points from Questus if they are below their max
con and have no trains left and fewer than 10 practices.

PC corpses decay eventually, after roughly 30 minutes of real time.
{x
(We do not have a morgue.)
