0 0 EXPERIENCE LEVEL XP~
Your character advances in power by gaining experience.  You need a set
amount of experience points for each leve based on your class and race.
 
You gain experience by:
 
   killing monsters
   being part of a group that kills a monster (if you are in the same room)
   improving your skills
   doing retrieval quests for Questus
 
You lose experience by:
 
   fleeing combat
   dishonoring (help '{CDISHONOR{x')
   recalling out of combat
   being the target of certain spells
   dying
 
The experience you gain from combat is affected by several factors:
 
   higher charisma means higher morale, and is a better learning environment
   a leader with high charisma improves morale of the group
   killing those aligned against you (good killing evil, evil killing good)
      will give you a very nice bonus.
   killing monsters higher than your level.
 
Groups:
 
   Groups split their exp based on your level in the group.  Beyond that
   they get both the morale bonus for a charismatic leader, and up to 20%
   bonus for grouping.  While the exp is split, a group of adventurers
   kills monsters much more quickly, and needs far less time to rest
   between battles.
~
