-1 0 WHO~
Syntax: who
Syntax: who clan
Syntax: who pk
Syntax: who immortals
Syntax: who tattoo
Syntax: who <clan name>
Syntax: who <race name>
 
WHO command shows the players currently in game. When the player is 
invisible for you, WHO command will not show that player.
 
With no arguments given WHO command shows all the players you can see.
'{Cwho clan{x' shows only clan players.
'{Cwho pk{x' shows players in your PK range.
'{Cwho immortals{x' shows all immortal players.
'{Cwho tattoo{x' shows players of your religion.
 
By specifying clan or race you can restrict list of players by 
specified clan or race.
 
An example of the who list:
 
{y|{G HER {y|{MBattleRager{y|{R PK{y |{x Bob the Destroyer
 
The first column shows if this character is a Hero or an Immortal. If 
they are neither it will be blank.  The second column is that players
clan.  Again, if they are not in a clan this will be blank. The last 
column has a red PK flag in it if the character is in your PK range.  
Read "HELP PK" for more information on PK ranges.
 
You can only see a characters title if they are the same class as you,
are the same clan as you, or are an Immortal or Hero, otherwise you see 
their race.
  
WHO arguments can be combined.
  
See also: WHOIS.
