Caltrops, fist-sized metal balls with four projecting spikes, were
originally used to impede the charge of cavalry in battle.  Samurai and
ninja have adopted and altered the technique, slightly, tossing handfuls of
miniature caltrops at the feet of their opponents.  The dexterity and
hitroll of the target is significantly lowered while the victim limps around
on injured feet.  
~
