-1 0 PERSONAL DESCRIPTIONS~
{Y======================{x
{RDescription Guidelines{x
{Y======================{x
 
{C1: Must have a description in between levels 15 and 20.{x
 
Why? Because it will keep you out of the description room and away from the immortals assigned to make sure of this. Another reason is that it is good form, as well as good RP and will get you more friends in the long run. Dungeons and Dragons denizens enjoy to role play and they'll role play with anyone who seems up to snuff.
 
 
{C2: After formation, your description should be no less than 5 lines.{x
 
Why? Five lines of a descriptive text will allow anyone enough room to properly identify everything about their character that they want other's to see. {RPlease try not to place personal items of clothing in your description. If you feel you must do it, please have a valid reason as to why you've written it in there. Using anything similar to, "Well, I wear clothes under armour because it's just how it was done back then." Won't really cut it. Clothing can be included in a description, but it needs to be simple things, nothing that would completely contradict the armour you are wearing.....{x
 
{C3: Before Creation, Try to come up with some sort of flavor to your character.{x
 
Why? Not only will you be able to quickly apply your description to your character, it will also give you an idea of what you need to role play with. Is your guy or gal a big person, physically strong, and mentally weak. Or is your guy or gal physically ok, and mentally excellent. Keep in mind, these key factors all determine how you role play your character. It wouldn't do any good to play out a mega-super strong warlock character whose as dumb as a pile of rocks. 
 
Playing that would mean that your warlock would never be able to cast a spell, and would be a better warrior than anything. Just as well, choose race and class carefully. Please don't be an Anti-Paladin troll running around with a tattoo of Eros. Itjust doesn't fit and takes away quite a bit from the purpose of religion. Though, should it be found that there's an unimaginable amount of logic behind the decision, I do not see why the tattoo cannot stay.
 
{C4: Have something incredibly unique.{x
 
