Since Rulers enforce the Law, an applicant must
be familiar with the Laws. You WILL be quizzed.
Also, since some miscreants continually seek to
stretch or abuse the Laws, be able to apply the
Law to any theoretical problem not specifically
covered in the printed laws. Flexibility counts.
 
Rulers must also  know the territory.  Know how
to get from any  protected area directly to any
other one.  Also, know all the home towns (i.e.
"recall points").  Know how  to get  from place
to place without having to consult an area map.
 
Finally, there may come  a time when Rulers are
called to protect Midgaard from invasion. There
are unfortunately many routes to enter Midgaard
without going through  the gates.  One comes in
through the sewers,  and there are at least six
other ways in (differing by the 'first' room in
which you arrive in Midgaard.  Be aware of some
of these  unhappy holes in  Midgaard's security.
 
But, of course, being a Ruler is not only about
knowing things and  being able to answer a quiz.
You must  also prove  your sufficiency  for any
situation in which a criminal  may defy the Law.
You will be sent on a quest much like Questus's
to prove your mettle, and to verify your skill.
 
If any pure spellcaster should express a desire
to assist in enforcing the Law, he must also be
able to meet  such challenges.  If he is unable
to win a fight head-on, then he must at minimum
be able  to survive the event.   Therefore, any
such applicant  must memorize  a transportation
spell before requesting admission to the Rulers.
 
Finally, when promoting  the Law, one must also
promote respect for the Law,  and this can only
happen if the citizens have a respect for Ruler.
Every judicial act  reflects on the entire clan.
Since a reputation cannot be measured during an
interview, an applicant must  undergo a minimum
one-week waiting period  from when he announces
his desire to join,  during which  his roleplay
may be monitored  either by  existing Rulers or
trusted non-Rulers. Only those seen to be stout
of heart, strong of mettle,  and slow of temper
can expect  to be welcomed  into the Ruler clan.
~
