92 0 COMMANDMENTS 'GOD RULES' GODS~
The Rules of Immortal staff
           
1) Do not abuse your power in any way. This include but not
   limited to:                                             
              
   Killing mortals or doing something that leads to a mortals
   death.          
   Cheating for ANY mortals be it your own or a complete
   stranger.[Giving an any advantage or disadvantage to a player]
            [over another or mob.]
   [Some froms of cheating listed below]    
   (Tanking, spell ups, altering mobs, or loading them for mortals,)
   (handing out eq, giving special privilages, ect. ect.)
       
2) Do not kill shopkeepers of open areas.. No reason to.
          
3) Do not use REBOOT.  <--- Note, simple English.
   Only with a DM's permission are you allowed to do this.
 
4) Do not give out free equipment.
   Do not alter existing equipment for mortal use. 
   Quests are fine but handing out items isn't. 
   If you wish to reward an item for a quest have it oked
   by a immortal over the rank of 96.
          
   A note on quests: Quests are a good thing, more or less, BUT 
   do not give out overly extravagant prizes.  Exercise some 
   common sense here folks. If you question you reward just ask
   a immortal over the rank of 96. Also, if you have permission
   to run a quest where the reward is an item, do not set that
   items level below 4 of its normal one.
     
5) Do not undermine the authority of a Dungeon Master or any other
   immortal of superior rank. They are that rank for a reason. If
   you feel that a given immortal is abusing there right or being
   unfair let a DM or higher ranking immortal know immediatly. 
         
6) If you see that someone has been frozen or nochannelled do not restore
   their priveleges without speaking with the immortal who did it. If that
   immortal can not be found, then find an immortal of high rank and let
   them know of the situation. 
   
7) Do not try to overrule each other, it causes more problems than it is 
   worth. If you have a disagreement with someone of the same rank as 
   yourself, seek higher council.  
        
8) Do not HANG in the same room as mortals. This is a DO NOT. Please
   stay in your area and talk and give help from there. You may
   hang with another imm (In the same room)or a hero in the chat room.
   Spending to much time in the mortal realms allows more room to break
   these commandments. We are not asking you not to speak with mortals
   but if you have business with them try to transfer them to a designated
   area first, also be polite. Check and make sure that person is ready to 
   be transfered. If that person doesn't respond then look for yourself, 
   before transfering. For the imms without this command use tells or ask
   an Immortal who does.
         
9) You are not allowed to QUEST. ARE NOT. There is no reason too....
   if for some reason you need quest points or something, ask someone
   with the set ablity to give you some. Simple as that.
                 
10) You cannot hold a rank in a clan other than "commoner." You also cannot have
    an alt in any clan ranked anything above second. This is to avoid a conflict 
    of interest. Also, clan business is mortal business unless you are told
    otherwise. So keep it that way.
           
11) Do not tell any mortal who your alt is, (or anyone elses). This is a big no.
           
12) You will not alter your mortal characters. You will not abuse your OOC 
    privaleges, (this meaning OOC knowledge, like other characters alts, stats, 
    etc.) Believe or not this is CHEATING.
           
13) No imm shall rename another imm. DO NOT DO IT. Unless you
    get a DM's approval for a rename you cannot be renamed. Also
    only a DM can rename an imm. No one else can do that, including
    yourself.
            
14) Using your alt to badmouth imms or publically disagree with an imm
    in an OOC context makes the whole staff look unprofessional.  It will not
    be tolerated.  You have plenty of oppertunity to discuss disagreement
    in an imm only fashion.
 
15) Do not ask for a promotion!
 
Notes:
      Disobeying any of the above rules are grounds for deletion. Other        
      punishments may be issued dependant on the rule broken and how many
      times you have done so.
                
      The commandments may be updated at any time, so check often.
