{CIn our world, there will always be those players who just can't role play to save their own lives. And then, there will be those players who know everything and anything there is to know about role playing. These role players are the role players we need to pay careful attention to.{x
 
There are certain things that you will need to consider before you begin your description. As it is, creating your description is the first step you'll be taking into role playing. You'll need to consider your characters race and class. Why? Because race and class determine your height, body structure, and physical appearance.  While the class you chose will affect your characters personality, whether or not he or she is intimidating or clean or dirty, etc. Knowing about your race and your class is the second step you'll need to take in getting prepared for role play. The best way to prepare, is actually, just to look at your class, find and read the help file for it, then find and read the help file on your race. This is a very obvious thing to do and should definitely be done by everyone, regardless. Keep in mind this one factor. Your class sets limits upon your description.
 
{CMoving on. Once everything is set and decided, what you need to do next is examine your characters race and class again, then examine your characters ethos and alignment. How does each of these things affect your characters RP? How does your character feel about the certain aspects of other races and classes? Or is your character just as mean and hateful to everyone and everything that isn't like him? There are things that you'll need to remember. Characters who are good may have a smile on their face because they are friendly, or they may have a frown on their face because they are the "starving artist" type. Something terrible happened to them, but it did not shake their fait and they still follow it religiously. 
 
And, also, keep in mind that an evil character might have a smile on his face - not because he's friendly, but because of some sick, twisted, perverted thought he or she might have just had. Or he or she may wear a frown because of a wrong they were dealt and it shook their faith from good and shifted to wherever they stand now. The hardest part about RP is deciding how your character will respond, act and interact with other characters. To shift back to descriptions for a moment, as I've seen it too many times:{x
 
There are some things that should never be included in your description. A description should only contain your physical appearance, how you walk, or the way your voice sounds. There should be no actions. An example of an action might be something like "He growls at you as you walk past" or "He charges everyone he sees". You can say, however, that he growls when he talks, or that when he walks he looks ready to charge. There can be no ansi art. Don't tell how you feel or what other people think. "He loves everyone he sees", or "You are scared at the sight of him" would not be allowed. While, "he smiles with love" or "he looks scary" would be allowed. Yet, you can mention some simple symbol, like a necklace or ring that signifies a clan or something of that sort. Finally, a description is only for how you look, not your history or purpose. People should be able to figure out your history and purpose by talking to you, not looking at you. 
 
{CRemember, it's just like real life. If I were to describe myself to someone, I wouldn't describe how I think, or how you would think about me, or actions that I do, or the clothes I am wearing. I would tell you my height, my hair, my face size and shape.things like that. The things you want to describe are the same things that you can tell by walking past someone in the mall. Though clothes are a part of that, the clothes don't make a person, since they can change clothes so easily. Just remember, first you want to think of what your character is like, then set out some simple words that you believe describe your character's personality, then use a thesaurus to find the most appropriate words, and finally write it all up. Remember, looks are everything, just like first impressions. You don't want to ignore them!{x
~
