The intention of the multikill rule is to grant some repreve to those who
do not enjoy being PKed over and over again.  In that vein we have established
that after you Kill someone you are not allowed to attack them again for
24 hours (real time) without a NEW reason.

Some people have requested we clarify this rule so that they may abide by it.

{WThough in the following we talk of {RKilling{x {Wwe really mean {rATTACKing{x.{.

{REvery{z PK must have an RP reason behind it.  And while we'd {Rprefer{z that the
reason were based on the victim's actions, we realize that most often people
are killed for their intrinsic nature (evil, elf, vampire, witch, paladin etc).

However, after the first kill you {Rcannot{x use intrinisic attributes as an RP
reason to kill someone a again.  Thus, an evil drow Warlock witch cannot be
killed by a good elf Barbarian first for being evil, a second time for being
drow, a third time for being in Warlock and a forth time for being a mage.

Nor can you kill someone first because they attacked you, and then a second
time because they are a vampire.

Once you kill someone, {Rall{x known reasons to kill them are {Rnullified{x.
You {RMUST{x base your subsequent kills on something they have done since the
last time you killed them.  The notable exceptions to this are if someone
posts a bounty on the victim after you kill them, but for something they did
before you killed them, and if someone is raiding your clan hall.

{r*{R NOTE{x: {Wthese rules are devised so that if you want to avoid being PKed again
        you should be able to, provided you mind yourself.{x

Okay, the following are just a few VALID reasons to attack someone again:

{W1){z {GThey attack you.{x
       {w(This includes {gautoassist{zing on someone, which is considered the
       same as typing 'murder player'.  It also includes any spell, skill or
       other action that may by its success or failure cause a fight to start.
       It also includes any action that directly impares your ability to
       attack or defend yourself, such as making you unable to cast spells.){x

{W3){z {GThey steal from you.{x
       {w(stealing includes killing someone's slave, taking items from a the
       corpse of someone they just killed, and taking their disarmed weapon){x

{W4){z {GThey attack someone in your group.{x

{W5){z {GThey attack someone in your clan.{x

{W6){z {GThey attack your clanguard.{x

{W7){z {GThey try to get you in trouble with the Rulers.{x
       {w(This does {gNOT{z include reporting your crime of murdering them.  But
       {gDOES{z include trying to frame you for something you did not do, and
       cases where the victim did not abide the law himself.){x

{W8){z {GThey convince someone to harm you.{x
       {w(This usually involves placing a bounty on your head.){x

{W9){z {GThey violate something you're RP bound to protect.{x
       {w(If you are a {gKnight{z and slew a vampire today, but the vampire is
       now attacking an innocent infront of you, you may slay the vampire
       as you now have {gNEW RP{z motivation to do so.  The same goes for {gSylvan{z
       protecting their forest, and {gRulers{z procecuting criminals.  Also, if
       you are a {gBarbarian{z and are clearly {gVISIBLE{z, and a mage intentionally
       casts spells in front of you (in the same room) you have a {gNEW RP{z reason
       to attack them.){x

{W10){z {GThey provoke you with insults IN THE GAME.{x
       {w(This is limited to {gSAYING{z something in the same room as you, in
       {gTELLS{z (unless they are marked with {g(ooc){z before the text of
       the message, or on the {gGOSSIP{z channel.){x

       Valid Provocation
       {g----------------{x
       Player tells you, '{GI was already half dead. You're pathetic.{z'
