-1 0 HOW TO CREATE A CLAN~
Starting a new clan is kinda like becoming a student at a zen buddhist
monistary; you show up declaring your enthusiasm and the monks rebuff
you, and ignore you for weeks.  Most applicants give up and head home
discouraged.  Only the most dedicated stick around to eventually become
monks; and that's the idea.

Constructing a clan takes some work on the IMMs' part, and distracts us
from our other duties.  We don't mind, as long as people aren't just going
to get bored and abandon the clan a month after we create it.  The
playerbase is such that even right now the clan populations are a little
thin.  So adding another clan is something we do with hesitation.  But
if you're persistant, and really prove that your new clan idea will
flourish in the mud, then we're ready to do it.

Here are the requirements for making a new clan:

{c1{D){x Your clan must have a binding roleplay idea that unites your peoples.

{c2{D){x You must have 3 or more members who publically pursue your clan's
        agenda for at least a month.  Please note, that it is easiest
        for the IMMs to spot persistant RP in the global channels.

{c3{D){x You must outline (usually on the forums for discussion) a specific
        roleplay goal for your clan, which includes who your natural
        enemies are, and what it means to fullfill your objectives.
        Clans w/o enemies are rather stale on an PK mud.

{c4{D){x Your clan must be based on interactions with others, and must somehow
        enhance the roleplay possibilies of a certain percentage of the
        mud's population.  If it is too limited, or too narrow, it won't
        look viable in our eyes.  The same goes for it being too general.

{c5{D){x Do {RNOT{x base your clan on expected clan skills!  You can not expect
        your clan to gain skills for up to a year after it is created.
        This is to deter people from creating clans just to gain new
        skills and with flimsy RP purpose.

Okay, after the above criteria have been satisfied in the eyes of the IMMs,
you will be slated to receive a WHO clan-tag and a clan-channel.  At this
point you'll be more of a "tribe".  If clan participation keeps up during
this period your next step is to find an IMM patron to build your clan
hall.

