0 10 sentinel ranks~
1) An unlimited number of members can fullfill the Patron, Elder, Veteran, Foot Soldier,
and Recruit stations.
2) There may be only one Leader at a time.
3) There may be only 2 Lords, 2 Ladies, or 1 of each (for a total of 2)
4) Each Lord or Lady may have as many as 2 Captains (for a total of 4).
5) Each Captain may have as many as 2 Lieutenants (for a total of 8)
 
Requirements to achieve a rank status:
1) Patron Deity: Be an immortal. The guidelines of help Sentinel apply to immortals, as well.
2) Leader
  a) Achieve the consent of the existing Leader,
  b) Slay the Leader and any of his followers willing to lay their life for him.
  c) Obtain authorization from immortal staff in the case of extended leave or
      deletion of the Leader.
3) Elder: Step down from one's duties as a Leader, Lord, or Lady
4) Lord or Lady
  a) Be (voluntarily) demoted from a higher status.
  b) Be appointed by the Leader, Patron, or representative Immortal.
5) Captain
  a) Be (voluntarily) demoted from a higher status.
  b) At the sole discretion of the Lord or Lady responsible for the Captain
  c) Be appointed by the Leader, Patron, or representative Immortal.
6) Lieutenant
  a) Be (voluntarily) demoted from a higher status.
  b) At the sole discretion of the Captin responsible for the Lieutenant.
  c) Be appointed by the Leader, Patron, Lord/Lady, or representative Immortal.
7) Veteran
  a) Step down from one's duty as a Captin, Lieutenant, or Foot Soldier
8) Foot Soldier
  a) Satisfactorally perform one's duties as a Recruit for one week.
  b) Be (voluntarily) demoted from a higher status.
9) Recruit
  a) See help Sentinel
  b) Satisfactorally complete the tasks assigned by the examiner.
10) Probation
  a) Perform intentional misdeeds against the ideals of the clan
  b) Perform intentional misdeeds against the clan itself
  c) Intentionally "bend" rules as outlined as help rules
  d) Perform RP actions disinclined to one's typical character.
11) Outcast
  a) Repeat offenders of the statute listed for Probation
  b) Intentional Breaking of Rules.
