0 10 sentinel conduct~
Words to live by:
{W1){x Sentinels are not only avengers, but defenders. But when one cannot defend the weak,
a Sentinel must avenge the plights of the tormented.
{W2){x While it is in our nature to rid the world of evil, Sentinel realizes that it is
sometimes more beneficial to not destroy evil than to destroy it. "Keep your friends
close, but keep your enemies closer." Good can be twisted to unknowingly perform evil
deeds, but evil can also be twisted to perform good deeds, as well.
{W3){x To maintain one's purity, one must not be tainted by evil. That is to say, it is
one thing to attempt to goad evil into performing a task, it is a complete other thing
to torture evil mercilessly, without proper provocation. It is to the discretion of the
individual what consists of "proper provocation," however.
{W4){x To err on the side of caution keeps one's actions pure, but to err on the side of
haste keeps one's intentions pure. If you feel you must "take the shot," then do so. Be
prepared to answer to any consequences. Likewise, if you fail in your duties as the
defender, you must answer to those consequences, too.
 
{cOOC:{x
{DAs a result of being a "good" clan, it falls on us to be looked up to by the newbies
of the realm. For this reason, these rules are in effect to better attract newbies, in
addition to improving the quality of life at D&D.{x
 
{w1){D People that are conceived to be level 30 and below are considered to be newbies.
Newbies, as a result of not necessarily being "set in their evil ways," may not be 
attacked on the premise of being an AP, Vamp, Drow, etc. Simply being evil isn't
enough provocation - but evil actions are.
{w2){D If you are compelled to attack a newbie, try to scare him off, and explain to
him why he shouldn't do what he has done, and issue any threats deemed necessary.
Killing is an option, of course. But if you do kill him, explain to him that you're
doing because RP demands it.
{w3){D Don't loot a newbie. If a newbie gets looted as a result of your killing him,
then you are obligated to get his original gear back, or help him upgrade from what
he had.
{w4){D Anything beyond level 30 is fair game, but for the slow learners of the realm,
have the patience to explain why you did what you did, if you are prompted to do so.
But do not feel you have to tolerate any sort of abuse from that player. Depending
on how that player acts, you might have to knock some sense into him.{x
