0 0 DRINKING ALCOHOL DRUNK~
The consumption of alcohol can have beneficial and detrimental affects
on your combat and other abilities.  How much it takes for you to get
drunk depends on your tolerance.  Those who are small in stature will 
be easily overcome by liquior.  Those who are large, or come from hearty
stock, such as dwarves, tend to take more to feel the effects of a good
drink.
 
Once you are drunk you may find it harder to hit your opponent, but the
wound you inflict will be much more deadly.  You'll also feel stronger
and a little more clumsy.
 
Mages will find it particularly hard to correctly enunciate their incantations
Those who channel their ki will will also have difficulty.  Clerics, though,
being drunk isn't exactly beneficial, have found it much easier to contact
their gods while drunk, than Mages do the Source.  And dwarven clerics are
well known for being able to manage both.
 
While you're drunk you'll also find that your opponent doesn't quite hit
as hard as you remember.
 
ALSO SEE: {CDRINKING SKILL{x
