test.  There were many {Gcandidates{x who lost interest during the process,
and showed a lack of {ypatience{x, a {rvice{x not worthy of a {yS{gy{Glv{ga{yn{x.  The tests
were constructed to identify such candidates and discourage them from
seeking admittance.  Those who passed all the tests set before them truely
deserved to wear the {gMark of the Wild {yEarth{x.

My applicants needed to pass all of the following:

{GApplication{x - all applicants were required to send a {rlengthy note{x to the clan
about their interest in guarding the Forest from poachers.  In this they
spoke of why the Forest meant so much to them and how they had come to
understand it.  They were to speak of their deeds in protecting the Forest
in their youth, and to the present day.  And they were to address their
commitment to the way of {yNature{x.

{GReputation{x - after receiving an application the {yS{gy{Glv{ga{yn{x Wardens were asked
to watch the applicant and observe his or her {cpublic conduct{x.  The
