92 0 ifrand if rand~
Sytax: if rand [{Gwhole number{z]
Exa. : if rand {G50{z
              
If rand makes the mud 'roll a dice' to check if
the number is equal to or greater than the 
{Gwhole number{x provided. So if you choose {G1{x
as your {Gwhole number{x. Then you would have no
chance of failure.
      
Why? Simple. The mud would roll a number from 1 to
100 and since you chose {G1{x as your {Gwhole number{z
then there is no chance of it not being 1 or greater.
The same goes for 100. If you choose {G100{x as your 
number than you only have a 1 in 100 chance of success,
making the likely hood of success highly improbable.
         
There are only 2 ways to use this if check. 
              
one) by itself: if rand 50
                say 50 or more!
                endif
                end
                    
two) with else: if rand 50
                say 50 or more!
                else 
                say less than 50!
                endif
                end
              
Of course you may use it with other checks. But to
keep this short I will only give 1 example.
                  
            if rand 50
            and name $n Daphais
            say Hello Daphais
            else
            say Hello
            endif
            end
The mud would 'roll' it's number then if it was
equal to or above 50 then it would check to see if
the target (the pc/npc who initiated the prog) is 
named Daphais. If so it would say "Hello Daphais".
If the target wasn't named Daphais or if the muds 
'roll' was less than 50 it would simply say "Hello"
~
