Drow, Wood-Elves share an acute attenuation with nature, and live in tribes.
The tribes themselves live a variety of housing arrangements, whether it be
high in the trees, in beaver-like dams on the water, or tent-like structures
that're easily replaced.  Wood-Elves consistently have earthier tones than
their cousins, skin bronzed by the sun, with hair ranging from copper red to
chestnut brown.  
